                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to
                        Lieutenant General <persName type="to">Alvan C. Gillem, Jr.</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">OSE 466</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-27">27 September
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Marshall desires that all action to complete the so-called reoccupation
                    (of Manchuria) program, that is the supply of ammunition and combat equipment to
                    the Chinese Government, be deferred until further notice from him.</p>
                <closer>For General Marshall: <lb/>
                    <signed>J. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hart Caughey</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Colonel, G. S. C.</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
